Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.team14.finalproject

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BallLauncher
    This class contains method for launching a ping-pong ball using the launching mechanism designed by the hardware team.
    Converter
    Utilities class that contains methods for converting distances and angles for the motors.
    LightController
    Controller that controls the robot's movements based on light data.
    LightCorrection
    Class that implements light correction for navigation using two light sensors.
    LightLocalizer
    This class contains methods needed for light sensor localization.
    Main
    The main class controls the flow of the application.
    Navigation  
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) position.
    PController
    Class that implements the Wall Follower using Proportional Control controller to avoid obstacles during navigation.
    Resources
    Class that stores all constants for lab 4 (localization).
    SensorPoller
    Class that handles which sensor to use (US Sensor or Light Sensor) and fetch data from.
    UltrasonicController
    Controller that controls the robot's movements based on UltraSonic data.
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    Class that uses the ultrasonic sensor to localize itself assuming the robot will start with its center of rotation in the bottom left tile of the field.
